users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: It is our sincere hope that Poland will now urgently address the key concerns identified by the Commission, in particular by taking urgent action before 3 July in relation to the situation of the Supreme Court judges.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: That is why the Commission has asked the Council to organise a formal hearing of Poland under the Article 7(1) procedure. Finding a solution is a matter of common interest for all Member States and EU Institutions.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The Commission must sadly conclude that the laws adopted in April and May are not by themselves sufficient to eliminate the clear risk of a serious breach of the rule of law in Poland.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Constitutional Tribunal judgements from 2016 still remain to be published without additional qualifications as to their legality, and no steps have been taken to restore the independence of the Constitutional Tribunal.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Recent changes do not eliminate the broad criteria governing the extraordinary appeal procedure, and maintain the 20-year historical reach of this procedure.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The revised laws offer no solution to court presidents already dismissed by the Minister of Justice or to Ordinary Court judges already forced to retire, including female judges forced out in breach of EU anti-discrimination law.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The politicisation of the National Council for the Judiciary still undermines its role as an effective safeguard of judicial independence.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: On 3 July, 27 out of 72 Supreme Court judges face the risk of being forced to retire, and the First President of the Supreme Court would have her mandate prematurely terminated two years early, even though it is guaranteed by the Polish Constitution.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The discretionary powers over the mandates of Supreme Court and Ordinary Court judges are still a key concern in terms of the separation of powers and independence of the judiciary.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: However, overall, despite these changes, key concerns which the Commission identified in its Reasoned Proposal remain unaddressed.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: 4 laws were adopted in April & May. I welcome the change which provides now for the same retirement age for male and female judges, and the willingness of the Polish authorities to discuss the other issues.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Today I updated the European Parliament on the situation with the rule of law in Poland. A number of measures have been taken by the Polish authorities since we last met.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The new asylum system will discourage abuses – with clear obligations for applicants and safeguards against “asylum shopping".
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: The new system will also be much more efficient and fairer, with shorter processes for assigning responsibility and processing applications.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: All Member States will be required to contribute and show solidarity. This may also take the form of financial solidarity.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We propose to introduce a corrective mechanism in our Dublin System. Each Member State's share will be based on clear and simple criteria.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Simple truth is that if Member States do not find common approach, not a single one will be able to handle  that responsibility on its own.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: In the past year a few Member States came under incredible strain. This results from shortcomings of the Dublin system in its current form.

users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Cooperation with third countries, protection in the region and resettlement from there to the EU should become the model for the future.

users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We need better approach to arrivals. Those who don't seek protection should be returned. Those who do, should be processed efficiently.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We must find ways to help people without them risking their lives in dangerous journeys. We need to take them out of the hands of smugglers.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: We need to make sure that people who need protection actually receive it. This is our moral duty as well as our legal responsibility.
users.description: Executive Vice-President for the European Green Deal @vonderleyen @EU_Commission | he/him
users.name: Frans Timmermans

text: Until we are able to build peace and prospects in our neighbourhood and beyond, people will continue to look to the EU for refuge.
